default2default              defaultCurrent proposalsdefault&#xa0;
default1.
default              
defaultThe current proposal of a fixed cut-off 
defaultbased on 
defaultthe length of sentence may be straightforward from an administrative viewpoint but is deeply flawed in its ideology.  It depends critically on the erroneous presumption that an offender with any given sentence length 
default(whether six months or four years or anything in between) 
defaultis as deserving (or undeserving) as any other offender serving the same sentence.  Th
defaultu
defaults such a 
defaultdeterminant 
defaultfalls 
defaultfirmly 
defaultin
defaultto
default the category of blanket decision making, the very conduct to which the Court of Human Rights is so clearly increasingly opposed
default in this area of human rights as in any other
default.
default  It must be assumed that there will be an endless trail of appeals against such a provision
default, and that it is only a matter of time before the facts of a particular case will result in defeat of it
default.
default&#xa0;
default2.
default              
defaultThe Committee should be very slow indeed to promote such a blanket proposal
default,
default 
defaultwhatever the sentence length proposed, 
defaultand should be looking for alternatives that might 
defaulttruly be
default regarded as proportionate.
default&#xa0;
