defaultwere below the age of eligibility to vote at the start of their sentence.
default&#xa0;
default4
default              
defaultThe underlying principle is of a scheme of eligibility based on a forward look
default 
defaultat the 
defaultright of (and need for) representation after release, not a backward look at the crime and an 
defaultarbitrary 
defaultextension of the punishment beyond release
default.  This is a proportionate 
defaultand individual 
defaultassessment of whether there should be a right to vote
default while in prison
default.  It
default 
defaultexcludes the serial sex offender whose current sentence just happens to be a short one.  It
default 
defaultexcludes the career armed robber whose current sentence happens to be short because the police were ly
defaulting in wait and thwarted the last attempt
default.
default  It makes a proper distinction between the repeat violent offender and the 
defaultsenior executive or 
defaultpublic figure who has committed serious offences but who is 
defaulthighly 
defaultunlikely to repeat them.
default  A fixed sentence-length cut-off is not capable of any such distinctions.
default&#xa0;
default5
default.
default              
defaultThe prescribed list would doubtless be subject to much debate and change.  Should serious fraud or perjury or perverting the course of justice be in the list, 
defaultor would 
defaultthese offences 
defaultbe covered by the criterion as to length of current sentence, 
defaultand so on.
